devdoc.details: A smart contract to store and manage immutable security logs on the Ethereum blockchain. This prevents attackers from tampering with forensic evidence.

addAlert(string,string,string).details: The main function to log a new security alert on the blockchain. This function can only be called by a trusted reporter.

params._alertId: The unique ID for the alert.
params._sourceType: The type of the alert source.

addTrustedReporter(address).details: Function to add a new trusted reporter. Only the contract owner can call this function.

params._reporter: The Ethereum address to be granted trusted reporter status.

getAlert(uint256).details: A view function to get a specific alert by its index. 'view' functions don't modify the state and are free to call.

params._index: The index of the alert in the `alerts` array.

returns._0: The Alert struct at the given index.

removeTrustedReporter(address).details: Function to revoke the trusted status of a reporter. Only the contract owner can call this function.

params._reporter: The Ethereum address whose trusted status should be removed.
